HEADWORD: Polycyttaria
<hw>Pol`y*cyt*ta"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>poly`s</grk> many + <?/, dim. fr. <?/ a hollow
vessel.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Radiolaria. It
includes those having one more central capsules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- polydactyl. = polydactylous. having more that the normal number
of digits; e.g. a polydactylous cat may have six or more toes on its
paw. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

